headline: CDW (NASDAQ:CDW) Reports Upbeat Q2
summary: IT solutions provider CDW (NASDAQGS:CDW) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 10.2% year on year to $5.98 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.60 per share was 4.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: CDW: Q2 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The Vernon Hills, Illinois-based company said it had profit of $2.05 per share. Earnings, adjusted for amortization costs and non-recurring costs, came to $2.60 per share. The results beat Wall Street expectations.

headline: CDW Declares Quarterly Cash Dividend of $0.625 Per Share
summary: VERNON HILLS, Ill., August 06, 2025--CDW Corporation (Nasdaq: CDW), a leading multi-brand provider of information technology solutions to business, government, education and healthcare customers in the United States, the United Kingdom and Canada, today announced that its Board of Directors has declared a quarterly cash dividend of $0.625 per common share to be paid on September 10, 2025 to all stockholders of record as of the close of business on August 25, 2025.
